00:15:11.950 --> 00:15:12.750 align:middle line:90%
emotions.

00:15:12.750 --> 00:15:14.417 align:middle line:84%
I'm just curious why
you mentioned fear.

00:15:14.417 --> 00:15:19.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I just asked
somebody what lotto was.

00:15:19.850 --> 00:15:21.120 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's uncertainty.

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:22.890 align:middle line:90%
But people enjoy that.

00:15:22.890 --> 00:15:23.690 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:15:23.690 --> 00:15:25.650 align:middle line:84%
>> They hope they'll
get the ticket.

00:15:25.650 --> 00:15:26.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:15:26.640 --> 00:15:28.620 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so fear is
just one example.

00:15:28.620 --> 00:15:29.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:15:29.420 --> 00:15:31.400 align:middle line:84%
>> What you're saying
is, we confront free will

00:15:31.400 --> 00:15:32.610 align:middle line:90%
at an emotional level.

00:15:32.610 --> 00:15:33.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:15:33.410 --> 00:15:35.020 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:15:35.020 --> 00:15:40.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the point is, that the
treatment that the uncertainty

00:15:40.540 --> 00:15:43.620 align:middle line:84%
is given by physics, because
physics discovered this,

00:15:43.620 --> 00:15:47.650 align:middle line:84%
you see, is to treat
it as something bad.

00:15:47.650 --> 00:15:49.750 align:middle line:84%
They shove it under the
rug and say, oh, well,

00:15:49.750 --> 00:15:53.100 align:middle line:84%
it's the third decimal point
